modules.description: Provides functions to create and manipulate message counters and logging tags, supporting increment, reset, and retrieval operations. Works with custom types for counters and message identifiers, enabling fine-grained instrumentation. Used to track function calls, measure performance, and log events in real-time applications.

Provides functions to configure and manage trace collection and subscription, directing output to files or standard streams. Works with output specifications that determine where trace events are written, including environment-based activation. Enables tracing during function execution with setup and teardown, useful for debugging and logging in production environments.

Emits TEF traces to a specified output using a subscriber and manages event collection through a collector. It supports writing to files, stdout, stderr, or environment-controlled destinations. Provides a scoped setup to initialize and clean up tracing within a function's execution.
